@node "wotsit" "What is it?"

  @{b}@{fg shine}@{bg fill}Starter v1.7@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back}

  Starter allows you to run a program by choosing it
  from a standard file requester...

  Now with @{fg shine}Locale@{fg text} support (English, Franþais and Deutsch
  catalogs are supplied).

  This version is half the size of the last version :)

  Version 1.7 dispenses with the mostly pointless "Run from WB or CLI?"
  requester, and now just runs in WB mode if there's an icon, CLI if
  there isn't - but see @{"Usage" link "usage" 0} for new CLI program information :)
@endnode

@node "usage" "Usage"

  @{b}Usage@{ub}

  Just run the program, either from Workbench or the CLI.

  @{fg shine}From Workbench@{fg text} :

  Starter's requester begins with the current directory.

  @{fg shine}From CLI@{fg text} :

  You can supply a couple of arguments :

    1) Starter <directory> - Starter's requester begins with this
       directory.

    2) Starter ASK - when you specify the ASK keyword, Starter will put
       up a requester whenever you try to run a CLI-only program, asking
       if you want to supply any arguments to the program being started.

    3) Start <directory> ASK - if you want to supply both keywords, you
       @{i}MUST @{ui}do it in this order!

  (Recommended : put it in your ToolsDaemon/ToolManager setup as a CLI
  program with the appropriate arguments :)

  NOTE - if you get the arguments requester, and decide not to put
  anything in, click on "No arguments" - as far as reqtools is concerned,
  clicking OK with an empty string is the same as clicking Cancel :)

  Select a program from the file requester.

  That's it :)
@endnode

